criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age between 45 and 65 years;

          -  Kellgren-Lawrence Grade I, II and III with knee osteoarthritis determined clinically
             and radiographically.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  history of surgery in the lower limb;

          -  patients who performed physiotherapy in the last six months;

          -  disease or disability which contraindicate the performance of the exercise training
             (vestibular problems, cardiorespiratory, rheumatic and neurological diseases).
